e aorta","The common hepatic artery arises from the coeliac trunk","The hepatic artery proper supplies only the right lobe","The common hepatic artery arises from the superior mesenteric artery"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecommon hepatic artery (image) arises from the coeliac trunk\u003C/strong\u003E. After its origin, the common hepatic artery gives off the gastroduodenal artery and continues as the hepatic artery proper, which then divides into right and left branches to supply the corresponding hepatic lobes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe gastroduodenal artery branches from the left hepatic artery\u003C/strong\u003E - The gastroduodenal artery branches from the common hepatic artery, not the left hepatic artery\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe hepatic artery proper arises directly from the aorta\u003C/strong\u003E - The hepatic artery proper is a continuation of the common hepatic artery after the gastroduodenal branch point\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe hepatic artery proper supplies only the right lobe\u003C/strong\u003E - It divides to supply both right and left lobes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe common hepatic artery arises from the superior mesenteric artery\u003C/strong\u003E - While anatomical variations exist, the typical origin is from the coeliac trunk\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe hepatic arterial system provides approximately 25% of the liver\u0027s blood supply, delivering oxygen-rich blood, while the portal vein provides the remaining 75%, carrying nutrient-rich blood from the gastrointestinal tract and spleen.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The liver receives dual blood supply from the hepatic artery (oxygenated) and portal vein (nutrient-rich).","The hepatic artery proper divides into right and left branches to supply the corresponding hepatic lobes.","The common hepatic artery arises from the coeliac trunk and gives off the gastroduodenal artery before continuing as the hepatic artery proper."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022.","\u201cCommon hepatic artery and common hepatic duct\u201d by Anatomist90\u00a0is licensed under\u00a0Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported license. (http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/). \u003Chttps://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Common_hepatic_artery_and_common_hepatic_duct.jpg\u003E"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61884"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18504"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21416"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21416","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21416"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/8HehWfzNB27SBIFWpRpjIRkNeF5bJq.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/8HehWfzNB27SBIFWpRpjIRkNeF5bJq.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":640,"height":480}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61884","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61884"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-03T11:32:12+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-03T17:57:14+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11233"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76375"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"se